“couturier” dressmaker, “vous avez entendu” you’ve heard (about him).

4 tu sais etc.: you know it will kill me.

5 Insiste etc.: quotation from St. Augustine.

6 Henry: Henry James’s style is suggested by the italicized “had.”

7 en laid et en lard: in an ugly and fleshy version.

8 emptovato: Anglo-Russian, rather empty.

9 slip: Fr., panties.

10 pudeur: modesty, delicacy.

11 prosit: Germ., your health.

12 Dimanche etc.: Sunday. Lunch on the grass. Everybody stinks. My mothe